com.list.alvis.o2s.core

Class O2SModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.list.alvis.o2s.core.O2SModel

  • public class O2SModel
extends java.lang.Object

    The O2SModel class includes functions to mapping and use Open API as SPARQL. You can load their ontologies that contains mapping information between Open API and SPARQL. And you can process user's request through Open API protocol.

    Since:
    2018-04-05
    Version:
    0.1

      • load

        public void load(java.lang.String filename)
          throws java.io.IOException,
                 ValueNotExistException,
                 OpenAPINotExistException
        This method is used to load ontology that includes mapping information between Open API and SPARQL.
        Parameters:
        filename - This is the file name to load.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If there is no file to read
        ValueNotExistException - If there is no value of Open API's title, name, and mapping SPARQL
        OpenAPINotExistException - If there is no Open API declaration in the ontology

      • execute

        public java.lang.String execute(java.lang.String openApiName,
                                java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> parameters)
                         throws OpenAPINotExistException,
                                MissingParameterException
        This method is used to run Open API.
        Parameters:
        openApiName - This is the Open API name to execute.
        parameters - This is the parameters to execute the Open API.
        Returns:
        SPARQL results as JSON
        Throws:
        OpenAPINotExistException - there is no Open API list or Open API given name as request
        MissingParameterException - If SPARQL has parameter(s) that not is(are) set value
